.TH LS 1 "March, 2026"

.SH NAME
ls \- list directory contents

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBls\fP [\fB-l\fP] [\fB-h\fP] [\fB-a\fP] [\fB-x\fP] [\fB\-C\fB] [\fIpath\fP]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
List information about the files in a directory, sorted by name.
.PP
This \fIls\fP only supports short options:

.TP
.B \-a
Show hidden files (ones starting with .)

.TP
.B \-h
When printing file sizes, use human-readable values like \fB2M\fP.

.TP
.B \-l
Format each file on one line, with details.

.TP
.B \-x
Format output into lines, rather than columns. This is the old default
prior to ToaruOS 2.3.

.TP
.B \-C
Format output into columns. This should match the formatting of most
other OSes, though we do not perform smart column sizing like GNU coreutils.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.IP 0
Normally.
.IP 1
If a requested path could not be accessed.

.SH AUTHOR
This \fIls\fP was written by K. Lange <klange@toaruos.org>
